%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22I've%20been%20job%20hunting%20for%207%20months%20since%20being%20laid%20off%20from%20my%20consulting%20job.%20I%20cashed%20out%20my%20401(k)%20to%20stay%20afloat.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Aaron%20Laniewicz%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c6c74fe99557fb1b08a152%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221152%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAaron%20Laniewicz%3Cp%3EAaron%20Laniewicz%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAaron%20Laniewicz%20has%20been%20looking%20for%20full-time%20work%20since%20Booz%20Allen%20Hamilton%20laid%20him%20off%20in%20August.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20he's%20cashed%20out%20his%20401(k)%20and%20collected%20unemployment%20to%20pay%20down%20debt%20and%20cover%20expenses.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELaniewicz%20shared%20the%20job-hunting%20lessons%20he's%20learned%20along%20the%20way.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Aaron%20Laniewicz%2C%20a%2040-year-old%20job%20seeker%20who%20lives%20in%20North%20Carolina.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20getting%20laid%20off%2C%20I%20worked%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftreasury-department-cancel-contracts-booz-allen-hamilton-tax-return-leak-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBooz%20Allen%20Hamilton%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20digital%20transformation%20consultant%20supporting%20government%20contracts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20my%20team%20began%20shrinking%20as%20our%20project%20got%20closer%20to%20completion%2C%20and%20I%20was%20eventually%20taken%20off%20the%20project%20and%20put%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-people-dont-understand-about-consulting-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20the%20bench%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20Which%2C%20in%20consulting%2C%20means%20I%20was%20no%20longer%20assigned%20to%20a%20billable%20project%20and%20needed%20to%20find%20a%20new%20role%20internally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20looking%20right%20away%2C%20but%20with%20shifts%20in%20government%20spending%2C%20including%20efforts%20tied%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-consulting-crackdown-what-contracts-are-being-cut-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDepartment%20of%20Government%20Efficiency%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20our%20government%20contracts%20dried%20up.%20It%20was%20harder%20to%20find%20new%20consulting%20projects%20internally%20to%20pivot%20to%20when%20one%20ended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20August%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eafter%20spending%20a%20few%20weeks%20looking%20for%20a%20new%20assignment%2C%20I%20was%20let%20go%20with%20two%20weeks'%20notice.%20About%20eight%20months%20later%2C%20I'm%20still%20looking%20for%20full-time%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20is%20speaking%20with%20workers%20who've%20found%20themselves%20at%20a%20corporate%20crossroads%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20due%20to%20a%20layoff%2C%20resignation%2C%20job%20search%2C%20or%20shifting%20workplace%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShare%20your%20story%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSechTVqVWQve8iqYssNriCXdtwwdgGRixNNZpmslSKBQqIJ8g%2Fviewform%3Fusp%3Dheader%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efilling%20out%20this%20form%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20contacting%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajzinkula%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejzinkula%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20via%20Signal%20at%20jzinkula.29.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dfa2ba00-b21e-4834-8252-c804d14583e9%5C%22%3EMy%20job%20search%20has%20taken%20a%20toll%20on%20my%20finances%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20live%20with%20my%20wife%2C%20a%20long-term%20roommate%2C%20and%20several%20cats.%20My%20wife%20and%20roommate%20work%2C%20which%20has%20helped%20pay%20the%20bills%2C%20but%20our%20debt%20%E2%80%94%20including%20our%20mortgage%2C%20student%20loans%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcredit-card-debt-trap-high-interest-rates-retirement-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecredit%20card%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20has%20put%20us%20under%20pressure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20laid%20off%2C%20Booz%20Allen%20Hamilton%20gave%20me%20a%20week%20of%20severance%20for%20every%20two%20years%20I%20had%20been%20with%20the%20company%2C%20which%20amounted%20to%20about%20a%20month%20of%20severance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20collected%20unemployment%20benefits%2C%20but%20North%20Carolina%20%E2%80%94%20where%20I%20live%20and%20worked%20remotely%20%E2%80%94%20has%20one%20of%20the%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eleast%20generous%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funemployment-benefits-versus-average-wages-across-the-us-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunemployment%20systems%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20maximum%20payout%20is%20%244%2C200%2C%20and%20the%20most%20you%20can%20receive%20is%20%24350%20a%20week.%20My%20benefits%20didn't%20run%20out%2C%20but%20I%20had%20some%20freelance%20work%2C%20which%20disqualified%20me%20from%20receiving%20them.%20My%20last%20payment%20was%20the%20first%20week%20of%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f06b1a14-e760-45a3-b40f-4f4933bc058f%5C%22%3EWe%20had%20to%20cash%20out%20my%20401(k)%20to%20get%20by%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20decided%20to%20liquidate%20my%20401(k)%2C%20which%20amounted%20to%20about%20%2450%2C000%2C%20and%20use%20it%20to%20pay%20down%20higher-interest%20debt%2C%20much%20of%20it%20credit%20card%20debt.%20It%20wasn't%20ideal%2C%20but%20the%20interest%20we%20were%20paying%20on%20our%20debt%20was%20higher%20than%20what%20we'd%20earn%20by%20keeping%20that%20money%20in%20savings%2C%20so%20it%20made%20more%20sense%20to%20take%20the%20hit%20of%20withdrawing%20it%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20our%20finances%20are%20trending%20in%20an%20unsustainable%20direction.%20I've%20picked%20up%20some%20part-time%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efreelance%20work%20through%20a%20friend%20of%20a%20friend%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20a%20full-time%20replacement%20for%20the%20low-six-figure%20income%20I%20was%20making%20at%20Booz%20Allen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a7601a90-a3f8-4ade-a97d-d80321c06e74%5C%22%3EI've%20focused%20on%20local%20opportunities%20to%20limit%20the%20competition%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20job%20search%20has%20gone%20through%20several%20stages.%20I've%20focused%20on%20roles%20centered%20on%20process%20management%2C%20automation%2C%20and%20data%20analysis%2C%20including%20ones%20where%20my%20experience%20with%20Power%20BI%2C%20a%20data%20visualization%20and%20reporting%20tool%2C%20would%20be%20valuable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20on%2C%20there%20were%20a%20few%20promising%20opportunities%2C%20but%20they%20didn't%20work%20out%20because%20not%20being%20able%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmother-return-to-the-office-commute-childcare-nightmare-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ego%20into%20the%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20a%20dealbreaker.%20That's%20part%20of%20why%20I%20started%20focusing%20on%20local%20opportunities.%20When%20I'm%20competing%20against%20people%20across%20the%20country%20for%20a%20remote%20position%2C%20the%20applicant%20pool%20is%20often%20much%20larger%20than%20for%20roles%20that%20require%20a%20local%20presence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fg5mgr%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Share%20of%20unemployed%20who%20are%20long-term%20unemployed%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22467%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20also%20started%20applying%20directly%20through%20company%20websites%20whenever%20possible.%20I%20noticed%20that%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20there%20are%20sometimes%20multiple%20recruiters%20posting%20for%20the%20same%20job%2C%20without%20disclosing%20the%20company%20they%20are%20hiring%20for.%20I'd%20go%20through%20the%20application%20process%20and%20only%20later%20realize%20I'd%20already%20applied%20for%20the%20role%20%E2%80%94%20either%20directly%20or%20through%20another%20firm.%20It%20was%20a%20huge%20waste%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20search%2C%20my%20best%20results%20have%20come%20from%20my%20connections%2C%20including%20friends%2C%20family%2C%20and%20former%20coworkers.%20But%20I'm%20still%20looking%20for%20a%20full-time%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22de19aef9-eef9-4828-b500-ff3cfe89a3c4%5C%22%3EWhat%20I've%20learned%20from%20my%20job%20search%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20job%20search%2C%20I've%20had%20interviews%20that%20went%20really%20well%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20have%20the%20years%20of%20experience%20they%20wanted%20in%20certain%20areas.%20In%20recent%20months%2C%20I've%20worked%20toward%20certifications%2C%20including%20a%20professional%20scrum%20master%20certification%2C%20to%20help%20bridge%20that%20gap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20done%20everything%20I%20can%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-resume-builder-shares-top-tips-for-todays-job-market-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eimprove%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20used%20to%20focus%20too%20much%20on%20results%20without%20explaining%20how%20I%20achieved%20them.%20Now%20I%20highlight%20those%20steps.%20Those%20are%20the%20details%20that%20make%20people%20want%20to%20have%20a%20conversation%20with%20you.%20I've%20also%20changed%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20to%20better%20reflect%20my%20team's%20accomplishments%2C%20not%20just%20my%20individual%20contributions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20piece%20of%20advice%20I%20have%20for%20other%20job%20seekers%20is%20that%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20should%20tell%20a%20story.%20When%20you%20approach%20it%20that%20way%2C%20it%20changes%20what%20you%20highlight%20and%20how%20you%20phrase%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20open%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-taking-pay-cuts-huge-numbers-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elower-paying%20roles%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20are%20more%20junior%20than%20what%20I%20used%20to%20do%2C%20but%20I'm%20still%20holding%20out%20hope%20for%20something%20that's%20a%20good%20fit%20for%20me%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20any%20job%20I%20can%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaid-off-booz-allen-consulting-job-used-401k-pay-debt-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774690141000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c6c75a445048b5f68bbc02%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaid-off-booz-allen-consulting-job-used-401k-pay-debt-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Since%20being%20laid%20off%20from%20Booz%20Allen%2C%20a%20consultant%20has%20spent%20seven%20months%20job%20hunting%20and%20cashed%20out%20his%20401(k)%20to%20pay%20down%20debt.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jzinkula%40insider.com%20(Jacob%20Zinkula)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20value%20of%20cheap%20weapons%20in%20modern%20war%20isn't%20just%20the%20low%20price%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226086%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20in%20camouflage%20stands%20under%20netting%20between%20trees%20under%20a%20grey%20sky%2C%20holding%20a%20large%20artillery%20shell%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c66ba2e7bca39c4656cb40%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224057%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkraine%20is%20showing%20the%20value%20of%20masses%20of%20cheap%20weaponry%20in%20modern%20war.%3Cp%3EUkrinform%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERussia's%20war%20against%20Ukraine%20has%20shown%20the%20West%20just%20how%20valuable%20cheap%20weaponry%20is%20in%20a%20grinding%2C%20protracted%20fight.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20the%20value%20of%20those%20weapons%20isn't%20just%20in%20their%20price%2C%20a%20former%20UK%20Royal%20Air%20Force%20official%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20go%20for%20mass%20because%20it's%20cheap%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20It%20enables%20mass%2C%20which%20produces%20operational%20effects.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-did-russia-invade-ukraine-putin-politics-motive-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efight%20against%20Russia's%20invasion%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20shown%20Western%20militaries%20the%20value%20of%20cheap%20weaponry%20in%20a%20large-scale%20conflict%2C%20and%20the%20advantages%20go%20beyond%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECheap%20weapons%20matter%20because%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-west-needs-more-cheap-weapons-counter-russia-and-china-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eenable%20mass%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20mass%20allows%20militaries%20to%20absorb%20losses%2C%20overwhelm%20defenses%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20go%20for%20mass%20because%20it's%20cheap%2C%26quot%3B%20retired%20Air%20Marshal%20Greg%20Bagwell%2C%20who%20spent%2036%20years%20in%20the%20British%20Royal%20Air%20Force%20and%20served%20as%20its%20joint%20warfare%20director%2C%20said.%20The%20cheaper%20it%20is%2C%20the%20better%2C%20he%20said%2C%20but%20the%20appeal%20of%20massed%20weaponry%20%26quot%3Bis%20not%20just%20because%20they're%20cheap.%26quot%3B%20There%20are%20operational%20effects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMass%20allows%20for%20failures%2C%20losses%2C%20and%20ineffective%20outcomes.%20Think%20cheap%20quadcopter%20drones%20like%20Ukraine%20is%20using%20to%20target%20troops%20and%20tanks.%20Many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwest-drone-training-sees-crashes-losses-part-process-learn-ukraine-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enever%20reach%20their%20target%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECheap%20weaponry%20is%20often%20less%20effective%2C%20meaning%20more%20is%20necessary%20to%20get%20the%20job%20done%2C%20though%20it%20is%20still%20significantly%20cheaper%20than%20some%20higher-end%20capabilities.%20Thousands%20of%20these%20weapons%20can%20be%20acquired%20for%20the%20cost%20of%20only%20a%20handful%20of%20exquisite%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20real%20value%20of%20that%20mass%20of%20low-cost%20weaponry%20is%20that%20it%20allows%20militaries%20to%20overwhelm%20enemy%20defenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20need%20to%20throw%20enough%20that%20you%20shut%20down%20their%20system%20and%20then%20exploit%20that%20gap%2C%26quot%3B%20Bagwell%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227823%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20in%20green%20gear%20holds%20a%20large%20grey%20drone%20over%20his%20shoulder%20as%20he%20walks%20through%20a%20green%20field%20with%20leaves%20in%20the%20foreground.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F697b53afd3c7faef0ecd271d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225282%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAllies%20are%20learning%20lessons%20in%20drone%20warfare%20from%20watching%20how%20key%20they%20are%20in%20Ukraine.%3Cp%3EGENYA%20SAVILOV%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMilitaries%20have%20to%20balance%20cost%2C%20volume%2C%20and%20effectiveness.%20%26quot%3BThe%20calculation%20is%20one%20that%20we're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20continually%20look%20at%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20decades%2C%20the%20West%20has%20heavily%20prioritized%20smaller%20quantities%20of%20advanced%20but%20expensive%20systems%20built%20for%20precision%2C%20not%20mass.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Ukraine's%20experience%20against%20Russia%20has%20forced%20a%20rethink.%20In%20this%20conflict%2C%20both%20nations%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanalysis-putins-ukraine-attrition-plan-seems-to-be-working-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Echewing%20through%20weapon%20inventories%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20fight%20that's%20defined%20by%20extensive%20use%20of%20cheaper%20weaponry%20like%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20war%20against%20Ukraine%20has%20pushed%20Western%20militaries%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnatos-focus-air-defenses-needed-from-way-russia-fighting-ukraine-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eboost%20their%20defense%20spending%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETroels%20Lund%20Poulsen%2C%20the%20Danish%20defense%20minister%2C%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20lessons%26quot%3B%20from%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20was%20that%20the%20West%20needed%20far%20greater%20quantities%20of%20low-cost%20weaponry%20to%20meet%20the%20demands%20of%20a%20large-scale%2C%20high-intensity%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine's%20defense%20industry%20leaders%20are%20making%20similar%20observations%20from%20their%20country's%20experiences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESerhiy%20Goncharov%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Ukrainian%20Defense%20Industries%20%E2%80%94%20which%20represents%20about%20100%20Ukrainian%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20previously%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20West's%20longtime%20focus%20on%20a%20smaller%20number%20of%20exquisite%20systems%20would%20be%20the%20wrong%20approach%20if%20it%20were%20to%20find%20itself%20in%20a%20protracted%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20need%2010%20Archers%20from%20the%20Swedish%20that%20are%20probably%20one%20of%20the%20best%20artillery%20systems%20in%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20%3Cu%3Ethe%20artillery%20system%20made%3C%2Fu%3E%20by%20BAE%20Systems%20that%20Sweden%20gave%20to%20Ukraine.%20Instead%2C%20you%20need%20200%20cheap%20howitzers%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Bohdana%20one%20that%20Ukraine%20makes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadvantage-cheap-weapons-modern-war-not-just-their-price-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774689601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c66bc6e7bca39c4656cb42%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadvantage-cheap-weapons-modern-war-not-just-their-price-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There%20are%20advantages%20to%20cheaper%20weapons%20that%20stem%20beyond%20just%20their%20affordability%2C%20specifically%20the%20ability%20to%20generate%20mass.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sbaker%40insider.com%20(Sin%C3%A9ad%20Baker)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadvantage-cheap-weapons-modern-war-not-just-their-price-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20%241%20billion%20fund%20manager%20who%20sold%2070%25%20of%20his%20firm's%20stock%20holdings%20says%20these%20are%20the%20opportunities%20he's%20waiting%20to%20jump%20on%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Wall%20Street%20trader%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20New%20York%20Stock%20Exchange.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c58d544133f63e1c778bda%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222668%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ENYSE%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EOne%20wealth%20management%20firm%20has%20sold%2070%25%20of%20its%20assets%20in%20recent%20months%2C%20boosting%20cash%20holdings.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEddie%20Ghabour%20of%20Key%20Advisors%20Wealth%20Management%20says%20a%20defensive%20strategy%20makes%20sense%20right%20now.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20plans%20to%20purchase%20beaten-down%20stocks%20on%20the%20dip%20but%20thinks%20it%20is%20still%20too%20early%20to%20jump%20in.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20investors%20are%20focused%20on%20navigating%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-volatility-200dma-iran-war-how-to-protect-portfolio-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehighly%20volatile%3C%2Fa%3E%20stock%20market%20right%20now.%20One%20fund%20manager%20has%20whittled%20down%20his%20firm's%20holdings%20and%20is%20biding%20his%20time%20for%20the%20right%20opportunity.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEddie%20Ghabour%20is%20a%20managing%20partner%20at%20Key%20Advisors%20Wealth%20Management%2C%20a%20firm%20that%20oversees%20%241%20billion%20in%20assets.%20He%20recently%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20his%20team%20has%20sold%20off%20roughly%2070%25%20of%20the%20firm's%20stock%20holdings%20and%20is%20sticking%20with%20just%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20gold%20and%20fixed%20income%20for%20the%20time%20being.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20think%20the%20market%20or%20investors%20are%20properly%20assessing%20the%20risks%20that%20we%20have%20of%20going%20into%20a%20stagflationary%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20everyone's%20holding%20on%20hope%2C%20like%20last%20year%2C%20where%20on%20the%20tariff%20tension%2C%20we%20had%20this%20quick%20V%20shape%20recovery%2C%20and%20everything%20was%20good.%20This%20is%20a%20much%20different%20scenario.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGhabour%20admitted%20that%20he%20takes%20comfort%20in%20the%20fact%20that%20his%20firm%20sold%20off%20stocks%20in%20sensitive%20areas%20of%20the%20market%2C%20such%20as%20software%20and%20technology.%20While%20these%20sectors%20took%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-cowork-legal-plugin-publishing-stocks-legalzoom-thomson-reuters-relx-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebeating%20prior%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Iran%20war%20breaking%20out%2C%20he%20thinks%20they%20are%20telling%20an%20even%20scarier%20story%20now%20that%20the%20US%20economy%20could%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstagflation-us-economy-outlook-oil-prices-inflation-shock-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eflirting%20with%20stagflation%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFederal%20Reserve%20chair%20Jerome%20Powell%20recently%20stated%20that%20he%20didn't%20think%20the%20US%20had%20reached%20stagflation%20yet%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstagflation-paul-krugman-inflation-economy-policy-jerome-powell-trump-iran-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20view%20shared%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Nobel%20laureate%20economist%20Paul%20Krugman.%20But%20Ghabour%20thinks%20that%20by%20the%20time%20the%20numbers%20show%20real%20stagflation%2C%20the%20market%20will%20have%20already%20fallen%20significantly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20would%20it%20take%20for%20him%20to%20deploy%20the%20firm's%20cash%20pile%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGhabour%20said%20he's%20watching%20for%20two%20key%20things%20that%20he%20says%20would%20signal%20conditions%20are%20improving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20need%20to%20see%20is%20we%20need%20to%20see%20the%2010-year%20bond%20stabilize%20and%20oil%20stabilize%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Ghabour%20said%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20move%20in%20the%2010-year%20Treasury%20has%20been%20%26quot%3Bviolent%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20it%20could%20keep%20going%20higher.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20oil%20market's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foil-price-hits-100-what-smart-people-are-saying-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Evolatility%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20also%20making%20his%20team%20nervous.%20Until%20it%20stabilizes%20to%20the%20point%20at%20which%20gas%20and%20diesel%20prices%20decline%2C%20they%20won't%20be%20comfortable%20adding%20any%20long%20positions.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20to%20say%20the%20fund%20manager%20doesn't%20see%20the%20opportunity%20to%20acquire%20stocks%20that%20are%20being%20repriced%20amid%20the%20volatility.%20Ghabour%20said%20that%20he's%20waiting%20for%20the%20right%20opportunity%20to%20start%20buying%20again%2C%20he%20just%20thinks%20the%20dip%20is%20still%20in%20its%20early%20stages%2C%20as%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20still%20has%20further%20to%20fall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20people%20say%2C%20'I%20want%20to%20buy%20the%20dip%20and%20take%20advantage%20of%20the%20opportunity%2C'%20yet%20they%20don't%20raise%20the%20cash%20to%20be%20able%20to%20buy%20the%20dip%2C%26quot%3B%20Ghabour%20noted.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20fully%20invested%2C%20you've%20got%20nothing%20to%20buy%20the%20dip%20with.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20his%20team%20does%20start%20buying%20again%2C%20Ghabour%20says%20they%20will%20be%20mostly%20focused%20on%20Big%20Tech%20stocks.%20He%20cited%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fnvda-stock%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENvidia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Faapl-stock%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EApple%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Famat-stock%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EApplied%20Materials%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20examples%20of%20stocks%20they%20think%20will%20benefit%20whenever%20market%20conditions%20shift.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20opportunities%20we're%20going%20to%20have%20sometime%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%2C%20we%20think%20we'll%20pay%20really%20big%20dividends%20in%20the%20latter%20part%20of%20this%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20global%20energy%20shock%20is%20going%20to%20create%20some%20of%20the%20best%20buying%20opportunities%20we've%20seen%20since%20the%20tariff%20crash%20last%20year.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwealth-manager-fund-assets-stocks-market-investing-war-iran-oil-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774689301000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c6a9f4445048b5f68bbae2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwealth-manager-fund-assets-stocks-market-investing-war-iran-oil-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Eddie%20Ghabour%20of%20Key%20Advisors%20Wealth%20Management%20recently%20whittled%20down%20the%20firm's%20stock%20holdings.%20He%20unpacks%20what%20it%20would%20take%20deploy%20the%20cash%20pile.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sobrient%40insider.com%20(Samuel%20O'Brient)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwealth-manager-fund-assets-stocks-market-investing-war-iran-oil-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22AI-industry%20super%20PACs%20are%20mostly%20winning%20so%20far%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Former%20Rep.%20Melissa%20Bean%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c2ad0de98a37a4841f3080%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222010%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMelissa%20Bean%2C%20a%20former%20IL%20congresswoman%2C%20won%20a%20primary%20earlier%20this%20month%20with%20the%20help%20of%20%241.1%20million%20in%20spending%20from%20an%20AI%20industry%20PAC.%3Cp%3ETalia%20Sprague%2FChicago%20Tribune%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAI-backed%20super%20PACs%20spent%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%2011%20congressional%20races%20this%20past%20month.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20all%20but%20one%20race%2C%20the%20AI-backed%20candidate%20moved%20forward%20to%20the%20next%20round%20of%20voting.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20an%20early%20show%20of%20force%20for%20the%20industry's%20nascent%20foray%20into%20politics.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AI%20industry%20has%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fartificial-intelligence-industry-super-pacs-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epouring%20money%20into%20elections%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%20far%2C%20it's%20mostly%20paying%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeading%20the%20Future%20and%20Public%20First%20%E2%80%94%20two%20rival%20super%20PAC%20networks%20backed%20by%20AI%20executives%20and%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20spent%20nearly%20%247%20million%20combined%20across%2011%20congressional%20primaries%20earlier%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20all%20but%20one%20of%20those%20races%2C%20the%20AI-backed%20candidate%20advanced%20to%20the%20next%20round%20of%20voting%2C%20whether%20that's%20a%20general%20election%20or%20a%20primary%20runoff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20still%20early%20%E2%80%94%20most%20of%20the%20nation's%20House%20and%20Senate%20primaries%20are%20set%20to%20take%20place%20between%20May%20and%20August%20%E2%80%94%20the%20string%20of%20victories%20represents%20an%20initial%20vindication%20of%20the%20industry's%20decision%20to%20wade%20into%20shaping%20the%20makeup%20of%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20first%20election%20cycle%20where%20the%20AI%20industry%20has%20decided%20to%20wade%20into%20electoral%20politics.%20So%20far%2C%20the%20groups%20have%20been%20playing%20in%20open%20primaries%20for%20seats%20that%20are%20either%20reliable%20Democratic%20or%20Republican%2C%20meaning%20that%20whoever%20wins%20the%20primary%20is%20likely%20to%20become%20a%20member%20of%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d2a74cfb-7b3e-4d2a-b3a2-31ae16eacb8d%5C%22%3EA%20string%20of%20victories%20in%20Texas%2C%20Illinois%2C%20and%20North%20Carolina%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20both%20representing%20segments%20of%20the%20AI%20industry%2C%20the%20two%20super%20PACs%20are%20very%20much%20at%20odds%2C%20with%20each%20pushing%20for%20a%20different%20vision%20for%20AI%20regulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20one%20side%20is%20Leading%20the%20Future%2C%20a%20super%20PAC%20network%20funded%20by%20a%20host%20of%20AI%20donors%20including%20OpenAI%20President%20Greg%20Brockman%20and%20his%20wife%20Anna%2C%20along%20with%20Marc%20Andreessen%20and%20Ben%20Horowitz%20of%20Andreessen%20Horowitz.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20group%20generally%20advocates%20for%20a%20lighter%20regulatory%20touch%20on%20AI%2C%20pushing%20for%20candidates%20who%20will%20be%20broadly%20supportive%20of%20the%20industry%20and%20tech%20innovation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Texas%2C%20Leading%20the%20Future%20spent%20a%20combined%20%241.4%20million%20to%20support%20candidates%20running%20in%20four%20districts%2C%20including%20Tom%20Sell%2C%20Jace%20Yarbrough%2C%20Jessica%20Steinmann%2C%20and%20Chris%20Gober.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGober%20and%20Steinmann%20won%20their%20respective%20primaries%2C%20while%20Sell%20and%20Yarbrough%20advanced%20to%20the%20May%2026%20runoff.%20Yarbrough's%20opponent%20later%20dropped%20out%2C%20effectively%20making%20him%20the%20nominee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeading%20the%20Future%20spent%20%241.1%20million%20to%20boost%20former%20Democratic%20Rep.%20Melissa%20Bean%20in%20Illinois%20and%20%24509%2C000%20to%20support%20GOP%20candidate%20Laurie%20Buckhout%20in%20North%20Carolina.%20Both%20candidates%20won.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20instance%20where%20the%20super%20PAC%20failed%20to%20advance%20their%20preferred%20candidate%20through%20the%20primary%20was%20in%20Illinois's%202nd%20district%2C%20where%20Leading%20the%20Future%20spent%20nearly%20%241.4%20million%20to%20support%20Jesse%20Jackson%20Jr.%20In%20that%20race%2C%20Cook%20County%20Commissioner%20Donna%20Miller%20won%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20fight%20is%20Public%20First%2C%20a%20super%20PAC%20network%20funded%20in%20part%20by%20Anthropic%20that%20supports%20candidates%20who%20favor%20a%20stronger%20regulatory%20approach%20toward%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPublic%20First's%20biggest%20win%20this%20year%20so%20far%20has%20been%20in%20North%20Carolina%2C%20where%20the%20group%20spent%20over%20%241.6%20million%20to%20support%20Democratic%20Rep.%20Valerie%20Foushee%20as%20she%20sought%20to%20fend%20off%20a%20primary%20challenge%20from%20Nida%20Allam%2C%20a%20Durham%20County%20Commissioner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20group%20also%20had%20some%20success%20in%20Texas%2C%20where%20it%20spent%20roughly%20%24830%2C000%20to%20support%20two%20Republican%20candidates%20%E2%80%94%20Alex%20Mealer%20and%20Carlos%20De%20La%20Cruz%20%E2%80%94%20along%20with%20former%20Democratic%20Rep.%20Colin%20Allred.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20three%20candidates%20have%20advanced%20to%20the%20May%2026%20primary%20runoff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20statements%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20each%20PAC%20took%20shots%20at%20one%20another%20while%20touting%20their%20respective%20wins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJesse%20Hunt%2C%20a%20Leading%20the%20Future%20spokesman%2C%20said%20that%20Public%20First%20had%20%26quot%3Bstruggled%20to%20help%20its%20preferred%20candidates%20avoid%20runoffs%20and%20win%20races%2C%26quot%3B%20while%20Leading%20the%20Future%20has%20had%20an%20%26quot%3Bunmatched%20record%20of%20success.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnthony%20Rivera-Rodriguez%2C%20a%20spokesman%20for%20Public%20First%2C%20said%20that%20their%20PACs%20%26quot%3Bmake%20winners%2C%26quot%3B%20while%20Leading%20the%20Future%20%26quot%3Bjust%20sides%20with%20obvious%20winners%20to%20rack%20up%20a%20'scorecard.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223c3a3bd0-2d31-491e-a741-13ea4505553a%5C%22%3EThe%20AI%20super%20PAC%20civil%20war%20in%20NYC%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20their%20rivalry%2C%20Leading%20the%20Future%20and%20Public%20First%20did%20not%20go%20directly%20head-to-head%20in%20any%20of%20those%2011%20primaries%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPublic%20First%20had%20planned%20to%20spend%20roughly%20%241%20million%20to%20oppose%20Jackson%2C%20but%20later%20opted%20not%20to%20do%20so%20out%20of%20respect%20for%20the%20family%20of%20the%20late%20Rev.%20Jesse%20Jackson%2C%20according%20to%20a%20spokesperson.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20one%20upcoming%20race%20where%20the%20two%20groups%20are%20fighting%20one%20another%3A%20New%20York's%2012th%20congressional%20district%2C%20which%20covers%20a%20vast%20swath%20of%20Manhattan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20that%20race%2C%20Leading%20the%20Future%20has%20spent%20more%20than%20%242.2%20million%20on%20ads%20oppose%20Alex%20Bores%2C%20a%20New%20York%20State%20Assemblyman%20and%20former%20software%20engineer%20who%20has%20champion%20bills%20to%20regulate%20AI%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20Public%20First%20has%20spent%20%24477%2C000%20to%20support%20Bores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%20how%20it%20all%20plays%20out%2C%20and%20it's%20a%20wide-open%20race%20with%20several%20other%20candidates%2C%20including%20New%20York%20State%20Assemblymen%20Micah%20Lasher%2C%20Kennedy%20family%20member%20Jack%20Schlossberg%2C%20and%20anti-Trump%20commentator%20and%20lawyer%20George%20Conway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20primary%20in%20New%20York%20State%20is%20set%20for%20June%2023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-industry-super-pac-wins-congressional-primaries-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774689181000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c2ad3d5b58f1f0f933699a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-industry-super-pac-wins-congressional-primaries-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22All%20but%20one%20candidate%20backed%20by%20AI-industry%20super%20PACs%20have%20moved%20forward%20in%20their%20respective%20elections%20this%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bmetzger%40insider.com%20(Bryan%20Metzger)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-industry-super-pac-wins-congressional-primaries-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I've%20tested%20countless%20sleep%20tips%20for%20my%20job.%20Following%20the%20viral%20Dutch%20method%20actually%20helped%20me%20feel%20refreshed.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20writer%20sits%20on%20her%20bed%20while%20wearing%20a%20green%2C%20black%2C%20and%20white%20shirt.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c436f248461c18d7be6141%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20said%20she%20has%20experimented%20with%20many%20tips%20and%20tricks%20to%20get%20a%20good%20night's%20sleep.%20She%20was%20surprised%20how%20well%20the%20viral%20Dutch%20method%20worked%20for%20her.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Lauren%20Jeffries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EI%20write%20about%20sleep%20for%20work%20and%20have%20talked%20to%20countless%20experts%20about%20how%20to%20get%20the%20best%20rest.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThough%20many%20experts%20suggest%20total%20darkness%2C%20I%20tried%20the%20viral%20Dutch%20method%20for%20a%20week.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELeaving%20my%20blinds%20open%20felt%20odd%20at%20first%2C%20but%20I%20woke%20up%20feeling%20ready%20to%20take%20on%20the%20day.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20weeks%20ago%2C%20I%20woke%20to%20yet%20another%20bleary%20morning%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-analog-alarm-clock-stopped-doomscrolling-improved-mornings-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%20turning%20my%20alarm%20off%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20frustration%20and%20asking%20myself%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20am%20I%20still%20exhausted%3F%26quot%3B%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EI%20mentally%20checked%20off%20the%20sleep%20hygiene%20tips%20I'd%20learnt%20from%20previous%20experts%20I'd%20spoken%20to%20(after%20all%2C%20I%20do%20write%20about%20sleep%20for%20a%20living).%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freference%2Fhow-much-sleep-do-you-need%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EEight%20hours%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20sleep%3F%20Check.%20Keeping%20a%20consistent%20bed%20and%20wake%20time%3F%20Check.%20Avoiding%20caffeine%20and%20alcohol%3F%20Check%2C%20check.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20couldn't%20understand%20why%20I%20was%20waking%20up%20foggy%20and%20tired%2C%20and%20why%20this%20feeling%20seemed%20to%20last%20well%20into%20late%20morning.%20What%20was%20I%20doing%20wrong%3F%20Wracking%20my%20brain%2C%20I%20went%20down%20a%20Google%20rabbit%20hole%20and%20found%20a%20sleep%20hack%20I'd%20never%20tried%20before%3A%20the%20Dutch%20method.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I'm%20to%20believe%20what%20I%20read%20on%20the%20internet%20(and%20I%20sometimes%20do)%2C%20those%20living%20in%20the%20Netherlands%20apparently%20swear%20by%20the%20simple%20trick%20of%20sleeping%20with%20their%20curtains%20open.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20advice%20goes%20against%20everything%20I'd%20previously%20learned%20about%20sleep%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-blackout-curtains%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20darker%20the%20better%20%3C%2Fa%3Eis%20usually%20the%20rule)%2C%20but%20I%20thought%20I'd%20give%20it%20a%20go.%20What%20was%20there%20to%20lose%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2239559b0e-c027-4c4e-8afb-067970a7b7fa%5C%22%3EMy%20first%20night%20trying%20the%20Dutch%20method%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20night%20of%20my%20experiment%2C%20I%20spent%20a%20while%20staring%20out%20of%20my%20bedroom%20window%2C%20watching%20the%20trees%2C%20illuminated%20by%20a%20streetlight%2C%20blowing%20in%20the%20wind.%20Eventually%2C%20I%20fell%20asleep%2C%20but%20admittedly%2C%20it%20did%20take%20longer%20than%20usual.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20when%20my%20alarm%20sounded%20at%206.45%20a.m.%20the%20next%20morning%2C%20I%20was%20wide%20awake.%20My%20room%20was%20flooded%20with%20light%2C%20and%20I%20actually%20felt%20refreshed.%20M%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-tracked-moods-every-day-years-happiness-habits-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ey%20mood%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20boosted%2C%20and%20that%20energy%20lasted%20all%20day.%20Did%20I%20just%20crack%20the%20code%20to%20surviving%20early%20mornings%3F%20Time%20would%20tell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224908%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20view%20from%20a%20city%20window%20at%20night.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c43835732a02451471330b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223432%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20said%20it%20felt%20odd%20to%20leave%20her%20blinds%20open%20when%20she%20went%20to%20bed%2C%20and%20found%20streetlights%20to%20be%20distracting%20at%20first.%3Cp%3EAbdullah%20Al-Eisa%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2279b9def4-48d9-461f-80a7-2f6d694ac8ab%5C%22%3EThe%20rest%20of%20my%20week%20was%20just%20as%20enlightening%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20continued%20my%20experiment%20for%20a%20week%2C%20and%20my%20energy%20only%20improved.%20On%20my%20days%20off%2C%20when%20I%20didn't%20have%20a%20set%20wake-up%20time%2C%20I%20took%20the%20experiment%20a%20step%20further.%20Recently%2C%20I've%20been%20oversleeping%2C%20which%20has%20made%20my%20grogginess%20worse%2C%20so%20I%20decided%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceo-wakes-up-without-alarm-clock-tips-become-morning-person-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enot%20to%20set%20an%20alarm%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20all%20and%20see%20whether%20the%20Dutch%20Method%20would%20really%20allow%20me%20to%20wake%20up%20naturally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESure%20enough%2C%20around%20eight%20hours%20after%20I%20went%20to%20bed%2C%20I%20woke%20up%20with%20a%20feeling%20that%20is%20rare%20in%20busy%20adulthood%3A%20satisfyingly%20well%20rested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20more%20surprisingly%2C%20I%20started%20falling%20asleep%20faster%20at%20night.%20It%20felt%20like%20a%20miracle%2C%20but%20why%20was%20it%20so%20effective%3F%20I%20called%20upon%20a%20trusted%20source%20of%20mine%20to%20find%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b22e223f-1381-4820-8aa4-d1be866c62b9%5C%22%3EThe%20science%20behind%20the%20Dutch%20method%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EChatting%20with%20Dr.%20Lindsay%20Browning%2C%20a%20renowned%20neuroscientist%20with%20a%20doctorate%20in%20insomnia%2C%20I%20learned%20there%20is%20real%20science%20behind%20this%20newly-trendy%20hack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20through%20closed%20eyelids%2C%20you%20can%20sense%20changes%20in%20light%2C%26quot%3B%20Browning%2C%20a%20sleep%20expert%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftroublesleeping.co.uk%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrouble%20Sleeping%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20me.%20Which%20means%20your%20body%20can%20detect%20the%20rising%20sun%2C%20even%20when%20you're%20sleeping.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20can%20mean%20that%20you%20are%20pulled%20from%20a%20deeper%20part%20of%20sleep%20to%20a%20lighter%20part%20of%20sleep%20before%20waking%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20adds%2C%20explaining%20that%20this%20reduces%20sleep%20inertia%20%E2%80%94%20the%20scientific%20word%20for%20grogginess.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20why%20was%20it%20easier%20to%20fall%20asleep%20at%20night%3F%20%26quot%3BBright%20light%20in%20the%20morning%20can%20help%20to%20anchor%20our%20circadian%20rhythm%2C%26quot%3B%20Browning%20says.%20This%20is%20our%20internal%20body%20clock%20that%20controls%20when%20we%20feel%20awake%20and%20sleepy.%20When%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Ffavorite-sleep-products%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecircadian%20rhythm%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20well%20regulated%20by%20natural%20light%2C%20falling%20asleep%2C%20sleeping%20through%20the%20night%20and%20waking%20with%20energy%20all%20become%20easier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20there%20are%20a%20few%20important%20caveats%20to%20mention.%20If%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20wake%20up%20until%20later%20in%20the%20day%2C%20then%20this%20method%20isn't%20for%20you.%20Also%2C%20as%20we%20move%20into%20summer%20with%20lighter%20evenings%20and%20even%20earlier%20sunrises%2C%20the%20natural%20light%20might%20not%20fit%20your%20schedule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20you're%20someone%20who%20naturally%20rises%20with%20the%20sun%20at%20this%20time%20of%20year%2C%20I%20highly%20recommend%20you%20give%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmistakes-youre-making-before-bed%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esleep%20trick%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20go.%20I've%20learned%20that%20darkness%20is%20overrated%2C%20and%20I'm%20letting%20the%20light%20in%20from%20now%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsleep-tricks-viral-dutch-method-works-feel-rested-refreshed-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774689121000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c43710732a0245147132f4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsleep-tricks-viral-dutch-method-works-feel-rested-refreshed-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20years%20of%20writing%20about%20sleep%20advice%2C%20this%20unconventional%20trick%20finally%20gave%20me%20the%20sleep%20I%20craved.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Lauren%20Jeffries)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsleep-tricks-viral-dutch-method-works-feel-rested-refreshed-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Great%20AI%20Deskilling%20has%20begun%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20thinking%20and%20problem-solving%20while%20looking%20at%20his%20computer%20monitor%20in%20a%20large%20office%20space.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%