s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-tools-are-deskilling-workers-philosophy-professor-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equietly%20deskilling%20people%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228f65759c-0b82-43ea-8239-17d270473010%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEarly%20warning%20signs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20not%20alone.%20When%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclaude-outages-anthropic-ai-software-engineers-developers-coding-dependance-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAnthropic's%20Claude%20went%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20some%20developers%20said%20they%20struggled%20to%20continue%20their%20work.%20Tasks%20that%20had%20become%20routine%20with%20AI%20suddenly%20felt%20harder%20without%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BClaude%20outages%20hit%20way%20harder%20when%20you%20realize%20you've%20outsourced%20half%20your%20brain%20to%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20Redditor%20posted.%20Another%20joked%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20guess%20I'll%20write%20code%20like%20a%20caveman.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoments%20like%20this%20point%20to%20a%20shift%20already%20underway%3A%20AI%20is%20boosting%20output%20while%20quietly%20chipping%20away%20at%20the%20skills%20behind%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22John%20Nosta%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6966318f04eda4732f2ef442%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221365%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJohn%20Nosta.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20John%20Nosta%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20Nosta%2C%20founder%20of%20innovation%20and%20tech%20think%20tank%20Nosta%20Lab%2C%20calls%20this%20the%20%26quot%3BAI%20rebound%20effect%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20when%20better%20performance%20masks%20declining%20ability.%20%26quot%3BThe%20skill%20set%20actually%20falls%20below%20baseline%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20The%20danger%20isn't%20only%20dependency%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20regression.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20AI%20systems%20deliver%20fast%2C%20polished%20answers%2C%20they%20can%20also%20distort%20how%20people%20judge%20their%20own%20abilities.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-can-make-you-better-then-worse-at-your-job-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eoverinflated%20sense%20of%20ability%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20Nosta%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20problem%2C%20Nosta%20said%2C%20is%20that%20AI%20reverses%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-human-intelligence-impact-at-work-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehow%20humans%20normally%20think%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20traditional%20reasoning%2C%20people%20move%20from%20confusion%20to%20exploration%20to%20structure%20%E2%80%94%20and%20only%20then%20to%20confidence.%20AI%20reverses%20that%20sequence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BComing%20to%20the%20answer%20first%20is%20an%20inversion%20of%20human%20cognitive%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20Nosta%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20that%20inversion%20becomes%20the%20norm%2C%20the%20stakes%20are%20larger%20than%20productivity.%20%26quot%3BHuman%20cognition%20is%20on%20the%20obsolescence%20chopping%20block%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2202b00400-684e-4cdb-9965-c7092d55e6fe%5C%22%3EThe%20illusion%20of%20expertise%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225700%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22people%20working%20in%20an%20office%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69866b97a645d1188188e8fa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223802%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20risk%20of%20deskilling%20is%20especially%20acute%20for%20junior%20workers.%3Cp%3EMaskot%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20work%2C%20fluency%20is%20often%20mistaken%20for%20competence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERebecca%20Hinds%2C%20head%20of%20the%20Work%20AI%20Institute%20at%20Glean%2C%20said%20AI%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-making-workers-feel-smarter-but-worse-at-their-jobs-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecreate%20the%20illusion%20of%20expertise%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20becoming%20harder%20to%20tell%20where%20the%20worker's%20knowledge%20ends%2C%20and%20where%20the%20technology%20begins%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20research%20details%20two%20potential%20outcomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsed%20intentionally%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20in%20areas%20where%20a%20worker%20already%20has%20expertise%20%E2%80%94%20AI%20can%20create%20a%20%26quot%3Bcognitive%20dividend%2C%26quot%3B%20freeing%20up%20time%20and%20sharpening%20judgment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsed%20reflexively%20as%20a%20shortcut%2C%20it%20creates%20%26quot%3Bcognitive%20debt%2C%26quot%3B%20making%20people%20faster%20while%20quietly%20eroding%20their%20skills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20difference%20is%20in%20whether%20AI%20supports%20thinking%20or%20replaces%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2219d9376f-8a2b-4100-a55b-3e10114d8075%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDeskilling%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20your%20career%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20risk%20of%20deskilling%20is%20especially%20acute%20for%20early-career%20workers%2C%20Hinds%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJunior%20roles%20have%20traditionally%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-deepmind-anthropic-ceos-ai-junior-roles-hiring-davos-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etraining%20grounds%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20break%20down%20a%20messy%20problem%2C%20fix%20what's%20broken%2C%20and%20defend%20your%20thinking%20when%20someone%20challenges%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20that%20experience%2C%20workers%20can%20appear%20competent%20without%20ever%20developing%20real%20expertise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20full%20impact%20of%20that%20shift%20may%20take%20years%20to%20fully%20show%20up.%20But%20the%20early%20signs%20are%20already%20visible%2C%20and%20those%20most%20at%20risk%20are%20the%20ones%20early%20in%20their%20careers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRight%20now%2C%20most%20professionals%20learned%20their%20craft%20before%20AI%2C%20so%20they%20have%20the%20baseline%2C%26quot%3B%20Jan%20Tegze%2C%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BJob%20Search%20Guide%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BHow%20to%20Talk%20to%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThe%20risk%20is%20with%20those%20who%20never%20build%20that%20baseline%20at%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Office%20workers%20and%20commuters%20walk%20through%20Canary%20Wharf%20in%20London%20during%20the%20morning%20rush%20hour.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659d3a12dcdb354a9855ca5f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOffice%20workers%20and%20commuters%20walk%20through%20Canary%20Wharf%20in%20London%20during%20the%20morning%20rush%20hour.%3Cp%3EVictoria%20Jones%2C%20PA%20Images%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBen%20Eubanks%2C%20chief%20research%20officer%20at%20human%20capital%20advisory%20firm%20Lighthouse%20Research%20%26amp%3B%20Advisory%2C%20said%20the%20gap%20between%20learning%20concepts%20in%20school%20and%20applying%20them%20in%20real-world%20work%20has%20always%20existed%2C%20but%20AI%20is%20widening%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20have%20to%20go%20put%20your%20hands%20on%20a%20problem%2C%20wrap%20your%20mind%20around%20a%20solution%2C%20or%20challenge%20the%20way%20things%20have%20always%20been%20done%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20get%20to%20ask%20AI%20instead%2C%20and%20it%20gives%20you%20a%20neat%2C%20tidy%20solution%20instantly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20shift%2C%20he%20added%2C%20is%20making%20it%20harder%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-use-entry-level-workers-poses-risks-training-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eearly-career%20workers%20to%20build%20resilience%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20some%20companies%20are%20beginning%20to%20reinforce%20that%20behavior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployees%20are%20increasingly%20being%20evaluated%20on%20how%20often%20they%20use%20AI%20tools%2C%20Hinds%20said%2C%20rewarding%20speed%20and%20output%20over%20deep%20understanding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAshley%20Herd%2C%20CEO%20of%20Manager%20Method%20in%20Atlanta%2C%20which%20offers%20practical%20training%20for%20leaders%2C%20said%20she%20has%20seen%20the%20push%20to%20include%20AI%20usage%20in%20performance%20reviews%20increase%20over%20the%20past%20six%20months%2C%20especially%20in%20tech%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226016%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mehdi%20Paryavi%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F695267da64858d02d217746a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224016%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMehdi%20Paryavi%2C%20CEO%20of%20the%20International%20Data%20Center%20Authority%2C%20says%20overusing%20AI%20may%20make%20workers%20look%20more%20productive%20while%20quietly%20eroding%20the%20confidence%20and%20thinking%20skills%20their%20careers%20depend%20on.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Mehdi%20Paryavi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20problems%20show%20up%20when%20something%20breaks%2C%20or%20when%20workers%20have%20to%20think%20through%20a%20problem%20on%20their%20own%2C%20said%20Sara%20Gutierrez%2C%20chief%20science%20officer%20at%20talent%20assessment%20firm%20SHL.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnderson%20felt%20that%20shift%20firsthand%20when%20he%20stepped%20back%20into%20his%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20aware%20of%20how%20it%20worked%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20didn't%20get%20those%20%5Bworkout%5D%20reps%20over%20those%20three%20months.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20prompting%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fbusinessinsider.com%2Fai-tools-could-make-companies-less-competitive-think-tank-ceo-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eleaders%20to%20rethink%20training%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Mehdi%20Paryavi%2C%20CEO%20of%20digital%20economy%20think%20tank%20the%20International%20Data%20Center%20Authority%2C%20said%20companies%20may%20need%20%26quot%3Bmental%20gyms%2C%26quot%3B%20spaces%20where%20employees%20can%20deliberately%20practice%20AI-free%20problem-solving%20in%20the%20same%20way%20you%20use%20physical%20gyms%20to%20build%20muscle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a7641274-a1b9-464e-b9bc-38a5ab0765cf%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'My%20swing%20was%20off'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnderson's%20experiment%20shows%20what%20happens%20when%20those%20mental%20workouts%20don't%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%20his%20experiment%2C%20he%20was%20proud%20of%20what%20he'd%20built.%20But%20when%20he%20stepped%20back%20in%20to%20make%20changes%20himself%2C%20something%20felt%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20compared%20it%20to%20watching%20someone%20play%20golf.%20You%20can%20study%20the%20swing.%20You%20can%20understand%20the%20mechanics.%20You%20can%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BThat's%20how%20I%20should%20do%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20your%20body%20knows%20how%20to%20do%20it.%20And%20when%20he%20finally%20took%20the%20club%20back%20into%20his%20own%20hands%2C%20he%20felt%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20swing%20was%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20writing%20the%20code%20himself%20again.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20like%2C%20'but%20I%20know%20how%20to%20do%20this%2C'%20but%20I%20couldn't%20get%20my%20body%20to%20move%20the%20way%20I%20wanted%20it%20to.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-deskilling-impact-on-worker-skills-productivity-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774689071000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a858befd4fbd083f298095%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https