r%20that%20to%20the%20taste%20and%20consistency%20of%20a%20ripe%20banana.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20avoid%20gluten%20and%20most%20dairy.%20So%20I%20have%20a%20special%20bread%20that's%20nut-%20based%20for%20toast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20lunch%2C%20I'll%20eat%20a%20piece%20of%20fish%20or%20a%20piece%20of%20chicken%2C%20usually%20a%20green%20and%20either%20sweet%20potato%20or%20rice.%20I%20tend%20to%20keep%20carbs%20lower%20just%20because%20I%20feel%20like%20I%20have%20better%20energy.%20I%20don't%20do%20well%20with%20heavy%20proteins%20like%20red%20meat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20large%20part%20of%20my%20career%2C%20I%20did%20experience%20an%20afternoon%20slump%2C%20and%20I'd%20have%20a%20snack%2C%20usually%20something%20sweet.%20I%20realized%20when%20I'm%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprotein-mistakes-health-issues-hit-your-goals-without-wasting-money-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eeating%20enough%20protein%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20getting%20about%2090%20grams%20a%20day%2C%20I%20don't%20have%20that%20slump%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22129653c2-88f8-4e48-8b6d-b6e7bc7b3bc8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20take%20breaks%20to%20reflect%20and%20prioritize%20deep%20work%20on%20the%20plane%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20day%2C%20I%20like%20to%20take%20my%20time%20to%20think.%20I%20am%20kind%20of%20a%20mix%20of%20an%20introvert%20and%20an%20extrovert%2C%20slightly%20more%20on%20the%20introvert%20side.%20So%20I%20try%20to%20have%20at%20least%20two%20breaks%20in%20the%20day%20where%20I've%20got%2030%20minutes%20to%20catch%20my%20breath%2C%20and%20reflect%20about%20things%20a%20little%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20travel%20about%20twice%20a%20week%2C%20and%20I%20really%20appreciate%20that%20those%20travel%20days%20are%20uninterrupted%20focus%20and%20concentration%20time.%20I%20can%20get%20a%20lot%20done%20on%20flights%2C%20so%20I%20really%20enjoy%20flights%20for%20that%20reason.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20often%20travel%20in%20the%20late%20afternoon.%20It%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20good%20time%20because%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20day%20is%20over%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20too%20late.%20I%20can%20still%20get%20a%20really%20good%20chunk%20of%20work%20time%20in%20with%20good%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22594e9edf-83d5-449c-a7df-dabd3ab39b20%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20work%20days%20are%20long%2C%20but%20end%20with%20some%20downtime%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20usually%20work%20about%2011%20hours%2C%20maybe%2013%20or%2014%20on%20travel%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20evening%2C%20the%20work%20transition%20is%20more%20fluid%20than%20it's%20ever%20been%20in%20my%20career.%20When%20I'm%20meeting%20with%20franchisees%2C%20we%20try%20to%20take%20some%20downtime%20to%20build%20those%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20being%20in%20the%20fitness%20industry%20because%20people's%20routines%20are%20very%20oriented%20toward%20health%20and%20wellness%2C%20not%20staying%20out%20late.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Orangetheory%20president%20Lauren%20Cody%20standing%20in%20an%20office%20with%20the%20brand's%20logo%20on%20the%20wall%20behind%20her%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c19d9e58b5806618e7d8eb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223001%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECody%20said%20one%20of%20her%20favorite%20parts%20of%20leading%20Orangetheory%20is%20that%20the%20community%20is%20focused%20on%20health%2C%20preferring%20to%20network%20over%20early%20dinner%20instead%20of%20happy%20hour.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Orangetheory%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20first%20started%20at%20Orangetheory%20last%20year%2C%20we%20had%20a%20leadership%20team%20summit.%20Dinner%20started%20at%205%3A45%20p.m.%20and%20ended%20at%207%3A30%20p.m.%2C%20and%20no%20one%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falcohol-affects-your-brain-body-cancer-new-science-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edrinking%20alcohol%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Everybody%20was%20ready%20to%20get%20back%20to%20their%20routine.%20It's%20a%20really%20healthy%2C%20wholesome%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222b0b526e-8788-4aa0-92c0-8f4c3b40e580%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20early%20dinner%20gives%20me%20time%20to%20unwind%20with%20an%20acupressure%20mat%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20it's%20about%206%3A30%20p.m.%2C%20I%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20I%20have%20that%20evening%20meal%20so%20it%20doesn't%20interrupt%20sleep%2C%20but%20then%20I'll%20be%20dipping%20in%20and%20out%20of%20work%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20evening%20until%20I'm%20winding%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20evening%2C%20it's%20just%20easier%20for%20me%20to%20have%20something%20like%20a%20hearty%20chicken%20soup%20or%20vegetables%20for%20dinner%20because%20it's%20very%20nourishing%20and%20warming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20winding%20down%2C%20that's%20the%20time%20to%20connect%20with%20my%20family%20first%20and%20foremost%2C%20to%20see%20how%20their%20days%20have%20been.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20I%20will%20find%20some%20time%20in%20a%20place%20where%20I%20can't%20be%20disturbed%2C%20usually%20my%20bedroom%2C%20shut%20the%20door%2C%20and%20bring%20myself%20back%20to%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20take%2030%20minutes%20to%20stretch%2C%20do%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freference%2Fhow-to-meditate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emeditation%2C%20and%20breathwork%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20I'm%20lying%20on%20a%20Shakti%20mat.%20It%20has%20plastic%20spikes%2C%20and%20the%20mat%20pulls%20your%20circulation%20to%20the%20surface%2C%20so%20your%20blood%20flows%20to%20the%20muscles.%20It's%20extremely%20relaxing%2C%20and%20when%20you%20wake%20up%20the%20next%20morning%2C%20you're%20not%20sore%20and%20stiff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22006538a7-03a3-4648-b69a-932e67f97165%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20love%20period%20TV%20and%20inspirational%20stories%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20usually%20don't%20watch%20a%20lot%20of%20TV%2C%20but%20for%20relaxing%2C%20I%20really%20love%20period%20dramas%20or%20historical%20documentaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20like%20to%20read%20inspiring%20books.%20I%20just%20read%20%26quot%3BIron%20Hope%26quot%3B%20by%20James%20Lawrence.%20He%20was%20a%20speaker%20at%20our%20convention%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20going%20back%20now%20and%20dipping%20into%20a%20book%20I%20read%2010%20years%20ago%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20Rise%20of%20Superman%3A%20Decoding%20the%20Science%20of%20Ultimate%20Human%20Performance.%26quot%3B%20It's%20fascinating.%20It%20goes%20through%20case%20studies%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-running-marathons-ultras-ironmans-extreme-fitness-competitions-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eextreme%20athletes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20how%20they%20get%20into%20the%20state%20of%20flow%2C%20and%20how%20you%20can%20recreate%20that%20in%20a%20business%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20don't%20have%20time%2C%20I%20might%20read%20something%20light%2C%20like%20an%20article%20that%20friends%20and%20colleagues%20have%20sent%20me.%20That's%20a%20nice%20little%20snack%20to%20mentally%20disconnect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20typically%20don't%20get%20into%20bed%20before%209%3A30%20p.m.%2C%20but%20I%20do%20try%3B%20it's%20usually%20around%2010%20p.m.%2C%20sometimes%2010%3A30%20p.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20it's%20Friday%20night%2C%20I'll%20do%20a%20bath.%20That's%20the%20biggest%20treat%20for%20myself%20%E2%80%94%20a%20full-on%20salt%20bath.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-orangetheory-president-lauren-cody-day-in-the-life-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774688581000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c19db65b58f1f0f93365f1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-orangetheory-president-lauren-cody-day-in-the-life-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Orangetheory%20president%20Lauren%20Cody%20said%20she%20loves%20plane%20rides%2C%20green%20tea%2C%20and%20history.%20Her%20routine%20prioritizes%20protein%20and%20energizing%20supplements.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22glandsverk%40insider.com%20(Gabby%20Landsverk)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-orangetheory-president-lauren-cody-day-in-the-life-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22China's%20'one-person%20companies'%20have%20exploded.%20An%20Alibaba%20exec%20explains%20how%20AI%20agents%20make%20that%20possible.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224724%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Alibaba.com%20president%20Kuo%20Zhang%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c47cf348461c18d7be6310%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223337%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlibaba.com%20president%20Kuo%20Zhang.%3Cp%3EHoracio%20Villalobos%23Corbis%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAlibaba.com%20president%20Kuo%20Zhang%20says%20AI%20is%20aiding%20the%20surge%20in%20one-person%20companies.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOpenClaw%2C%20an%20AI%20agent%2C%20has%20helped%20boost%20the%20trend%20in%20China.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAlibaba.com%20faces%20tariff-related%20challenges.%20Zhang%20says%20he%20focuses%20on%20two%20things%20to%20navigate%20them.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20seen%20an%20explosion%20in%20%26quot%3Bone-person%20companies%26quot%3B%20thanks%20to%20a%20little%20help%20from%20AI%20agents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlibaba.com%20president%20Kuo%20Zhang%20told%20Business%20Insider%20he%20has%20seen%20this%20growth%20firsthand%2C%20estimating%20that%2030%25%20to%2040%25%20of%20the%20e-commerce%20platform's%20customers%20are%20%26quot%3Bsolo%20entrepreneurs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20previously%20reported%20on%20the%20rise%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-openclaw-cash-subsidies-housing-office-startups-developers-raise-lobster-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone-person%20companies%2C%20or%20OPCs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20rely%20on%20AI%20tools%20such%20as%20agents%20and%20vibe-coding%20technology%20to%20build%20their%20businesses%20without%20hiring%20other%20employees.%20Some%20Chinese%20cities%20are%20attracting%20these%20startups%20by%20offering%20free%20housing%2C%20rent-free%20offices%2C%20and%20subsidies%20of%20up%20to%20%24720%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZhang%20said%20AI%20agents%20have%20helped%20make%20these%20types%20of%20startups%20possible.%20He%20runs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoutheast-asia-aws-alibaba-amazon-web-services-cloud-2021-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAlibaba.com%2C%20the%20Chinese%20cloud%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20retail%20giant's%20e-commerce%20platform%20that%20connects%20buyers%20and%20suppliers.%20While%20most%20of%20its%20customers%20are%20from%20China%2C%20it's%20also%20growing%20its%20customer%20base%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Europe%2C%20Latin%20America%2C%20Southeast%20Asia%2C%20and%20other%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne-person%20companies%20face%20barriers%20to%20building%20their%20business.%20Tasks%20like%20uploading%20products%20to%20different%20sites%2C%20managing%20social%20accounts%2C%20and%20handling%20customer%20complaints%20are%20%26quot%3Beasy%20for%20a%20big%20company%26quot%3B%20but%20harder%20for%20small%20businesses%2C%20Zhang%20said.%20While%20these%20tasks%20may%20not%20be%20the%20expertise%20of%20small%20businesses%2C%20they%20are%20%26quot%3Bessential%20for%20success%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgents%20can%20help%20with%20some%20of%20that%20grunt%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInstead%20of%20taking%20the%20place%20of%20the%20human%20beings%2C%20actually%2C%20they%20are%20the%20employees%20of%20that%20solo%20entrepreneur%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhang%20said%20of%20AI%20agents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlibaba.com%20recently%20launched%20Accio%20Work%2C%20an%20AI%20agent%20designed%20for%20small%20businesses%2C%20including%20one-person%20companies.%20It%20can%20help%20companies%20manage%20daily%20e-commerce%20operations%2C%20including%20customer%20service%2C%20tax%20compliance%2C%20marketing%2C%20logistics%2C%20product%20listings%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20in%20lack%20of%20help%20or%20tax%20support.%20And%20now%2C%20AI%20is%20very%20easy%20to%20use.%20It's%20very%20easy%20to%20adopt%20and%20to%20understand%20everything%20is%20going%20to%20change%20that%20perspective%2C%20and%20we%20think%20they%20can%20benefit%20from%20them%20the%20most%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhang%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlibaba.com's%20main%20Accio%20agent%20first%20launched%20in%20late%202024%20and%20now%20has%2010%20million%20active%20users%20a%20month%2C%20according%20to%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bb749375-eb97-4244-91e0-31a95db61acf%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EChina's%20OpenClaw%20craze%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rise%20of%20OPCs%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-openclaw-craze-lobster-stock-trading-blind-dates-cyber-pets-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboosted%20by%20OpenClaw%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20open-source%20AI%20agent%20that%20has%20become%20wildly%20popular%20in%20China.%20The%20craze%20has%20sparked%20a%20sort%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-big-tech-openclaw-lobster-gold-rush-tencent-alibaba-bytedance-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenClaw%20gold%20rush%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20spawned%20quirky%20agents%20for%20stock%20trading%20and%20setting%20up%20blind%20dates.%20Many%20OPCs%20have%20also%20built%20businesses%20using%20the%20OpenClaw%20agent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZhang%20says%20that%20the%20rise%20in%20OpenClaw%20has%20helped%20educate%20the%20market%20about%20AI%20agents.%20Alibaba%20itself%20introduced%20JVS%20Claw%2C%20a%20mobile%20app%20to%20help%20users%20install%20and%20deploy%20OpenClaw%20more%20easily.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompared%20to%20China%2C%20Zhang%20said%20American%20users%20are%20less%20educated%20about%20OpenClaw%20and%20that%20there's%20a%20smaller%20scene%20around%20it.%20That%20said%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-openclaw-lobster-craze-uninstall-ai-agent-paid-side-hustle-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenClaw%20has%20issues%20with%20security%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20return%20on%20investment%2C%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20some%20customers%20have%20spent%20%26quot%3Bhundreds%20of%20US%20dollars%20for%20tokens%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20when%20they%20don't%20get%20the%20results%20they%20want%20from%20using%20agents%2C%20they%20quit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20it's%20important%20for%20agents%20to%20be%20user-friendly%2C%20secure%2C%20and%20easy%20for%20customers%20to%20get%20started%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20go%20to%20SMBs%2C%20you%20ask%20about%20all%20the%20fancy%20terms%20about%20AI%2C%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-compute-compensation-software-engineers-greg-brockman-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etoken%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%20cloud%2C%20like%20open%20cloud%2C%20probably%20they've%20never%20heard%20about%20that%2C%20and%20what%20they%20care%20most%20is%20about%20how%20these%20tools%20can%20help%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhang%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f0d147c9-fff0-415b-b538-92a232ca4d8c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlibaba%20faces%20changing%20tariff%20policies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlibaba.com%20and%20businesses%20on%20the%20e-commerce%20platform%20face%20another%20major%20challenge%3A%20navigating%20a%20constantly%20changing%20tariff%20landscape.%20Zhang%20first%20became%20president%20of%20Alibaba.com%20in%202017%2C%20during%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20first%20term.%20As%20policies%20change%2C%20Zhang%20said%20it%20helps%20to%20focus%20on%20two%20things%3A%20serving%20customers%20based%20on%20supply%20and%20demand%2C%20and%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTechnology%20changes%20on%20a%20daily%20basis%2C%20so%20I've%20learn%20a%20lot%20from%20the%20tech%20companies%2C%20and%20from%20our%20SMBs.%20They%20will%20tell%20us%20what%20they%20need%20and%20how%20we%20can%20leverage%20tech%20the%20best%20to%20help%20them%20on%20a%20daily%20basis%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhang%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20rest%2C%20I%20say%2C%20is%20noise%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BJust%20follow%20all%20the%20rules%2C%20and%20we%20follow%20all%20the%20rules%20in%20the%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Armchan%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ermchan%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Eor%20Signal%20at%20rosal.13.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%2C%20a%20nonwork%20WiFi%20network%2C%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ehere's%20our%20guide%20to%20sharing%20information%20securely%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-agents-one-person-companies-china-openclaw-alibaba-president-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774688401000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c47efa732a0245147134be%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-agents-one-person-companies-china-openclaw-alibaba-president-2026